          "threat": "A spoofing vulnerability exists in the way Windows CryptoAPI (Crypt32.dll) validates Elliptic Curve Cryptography (ECC) certificates.<P>\nThe security update addresses the vulnerability by ensuring that Windows CryptoAPI completely validates ECC certificates.<P>\nThe KB Articles associated with the update:<BR>\n<A HREF=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4528760\" TARGET=\"_blank\">KB4528760</A><BR>\n<A HREF=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4534271\" TARGET=\"_blank\">KB4534271</A><BR>\n<A HREF=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4534273\" TARGET=\"_blank\">KB4534273</A><BR>\n<A HREF=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4534276\" TARGET=\"_blank\">KB4534276</A><BR>\n<A HREF=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4534293\" TARGET=\"_blank\">KB4534293</A><BR>\n<A HREF=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4534306\" TARGET=\"_blank\">KB4534306</A><BR><P>\n<P>QID Detection Logic (Authenticated): <BR>\n<P>The following versions of \"crypt32.dll\" with their corresponding KBs are verified:<BR>\nKB4528760 - 10.0.18362.592<BR>\nKB4534271 - 10.0.14393.3442<BR>\nKB4534273 - 10.0.17763.973<BR>\nKB4534276 - 10.0.16299.1622 <BR>\nKB4534293 - 10.0.17134.1246 <BR>\nKB4534306 - 10.0.10240.18452<BR>\n\n",
          "vendorReferences": [
